President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has proclaimed November 20, 2023, as National Child's Day, emphasizing the importance of investing in the future of America's children. He highlights the achievements and potential of today's youth, who are leading the way in addressing critical issues such as climate change and gun violence. The administration has allocated billions of dollars towards improving schools, expanding access to high-speed internet, and prioritizing the health and safety of children. Efforts include reducing child poverty, improving healthcare affordability, providing nutritious meals, and promoting LGBTQI+ rights. President Biden also emphasizes the need to address mental health, make the internet safer for children, and tackle climate change through significant investments. The proclamation calls upon all Americans to observe National Child's Day with appropriate programs and activities.